items.name: LogSentry
items.description: LogSentry is a lightweight Bash utility designed to monitor system and application log files in real time. It automatically detects new entries, highlights patterns, and can trigger alerts for suspicious or critical log messages.

items.name: -FileGuardian
items.description: Lightweight Bash-based file integrity & tamper detection tool. Generates SHA256 checksums for all files in a folder to create a baseline, then compares future scans to detect modifications, deletions, or new files. Outputs both human-readable terminal alerts with ASCII art and structured JSON reports for automation or logging.

items.name: TermSpace
items.description: TermSpace is a minimal retro-style starfield animation written entirely in Bash, designed to run right in your terminal.

items.name: procwatch.sh
items.description: SysMon is a lightweight Bash-based real-time monitoring tool for Linux systems. It provides live updates of CPU usage, memory consumption, disk usage, and top processes without requiring any heavy dependencies. Designed for speed and simplicity, SysMon is ideal for quick performance checks and automated logging.
